q {
Q:"If \\(\\vec{V}=[2,1,3]\\) and \\(\\vec{W}=[-1,4,0]\\), then \\(|\\vec{V}-2\\vec{W}|\\) is:"
A:"b"
O:a) "\\(\\sqrt{76}\\)", b) "\\(\\sqrt{74}\\)", c) "\\(\\sqrt{89}\\)", d) "0"
R:"First compute \\(\\vec{V}-2\\vec{W} = [2,1,3] - 2[-1,4,0] = [2+2, 1-8, 3-0] = [4,-7,3]\\). The magnitude is \\(\\sqrt{4^2 + (-7)^2 + 3^2} = \\sqrt{16 + 49 + 9} = \\sqrt{74}\\)."
}

q {
Q:"The projection of \\(\\vec{a} = \\hat{i} - 2\\hat{j} + \\hat{k}\\) along \\(\\vec{b} = 4\\hat{i} - 4\\hat{j} + 7\\hat{k}\\) is:"
A:"d"
O:a) "\\(\\frac{19}{8}\\)", b) "\\(\\frac{9}{19}\\)", c) "\\(\\frac{8}{19}\\)", d) "\\(\\frac{19}{9}\\)"
R:"Scalar projection formula: \\(\\frac{\\vec{a} \\cdot \\vec{b}}{|\\vec{b}|}\\). \\(\\vec{a} \\cdot \\vec{b} = 4 + 8 + 7 = 19\\). \\(|\\vec{b}| = \\sqrt{16+16+49} = \\sqrt{81} = 9\\). Thus, projection = \\(\\frac{19}{9}\\)."
}

q {
Q:"If \\(\\vec{u} = -\\hat{i} + 2\\hat{j} + 4\\hat{k}\\) and \\(\\vec{v} = 2\\hat{i} - \\hat{j} + 4\\hat{k}\\) are two adjacent sides of a parallelogram, then the area of the parallelogram is:"
A:"c"
O:a) "\\(\\sqrt{290}\\)", b) "\\(\\sqrt{279}\\)", c) "\\(\\sqrt{297}\\)", d) "0"
R:"Area = \\(|\\vec{u} \\times \\vec{v}|\\). \\(\\vec{u} \\times \\vec{v} = \\begin{vmatrix} \\hat{i} & \\hat{j} & \\hat{k} \\\\ -1 & 2 & 4 \\\\ 2 & -1 & 4 \\end{vmatrix} = \\hat{i}(8+4) - \\hat{j}(-4-8) + \\hat{k}(1-4) = 12\\hat{i} + 12\\hat{j} - 3\\hat{k}\\). Magnitude = \\(\\sqrt{144+144+9} = \\sqrt{297}\\)."
}

q {
Q:"The value of \\(3\\hat{j} \\cdot (\\hat{k} + \\hat{i})\\) is:"
A:"d"
O:a) "3", b) "4", c) "6", d) "0"
R:"Distribute the dot product: \\(3\\hat{j} \\cdot \\hat{k} + 3\\hat{j} \\cdot \\hat{i}\\). Since orthogonal unit vectors have a dot product of 0, the result is \\(0 + 0 = 0\\)."
}

q {
Q:"A vector of magnitude 5 and perpendicular to \\(\\vec{a} = \\hat{i} + 3\\hat{j} - \\hat{k}\\) and \\(\\vec{b} = 3\\hat{i} - \\hat{j}\\) is:"
A:"a"
O:a) "\\(\\frac{5}{\\sqrt{110}}(-\\hat{i} - 3\\hat{j} - 10\\hat{k})\\)", b) "\\(\\frac{5}{\\sqrt{17}}(-\\hat{i} - 3\\hat{j} - 10\\hat{k})\\)", c) "\\(\\frac{5}{\\sqrt{110}}(-\\hat{i} + 3\\hat{j} - 10\\hat{k})\\)", d) "\\(\\frac{5}{\\sqrt{17}}(-\\hat{i} + 3\\hat{j} - 10\\hat{k})\\)"
R:"Perpendicular vector = \\(\\vec{a} \\times \\vec{b} = \\begin{vmatrix} \\hat{i} & \\hat{j} & \\hat{k} \\\\ 1 & 3 & -1 \\\\ 3 & -1 & 0 \\end{vmatrix} = -\\hat{i} - 3\\hat{j} - 10\\hat{k}\\). Its magnitude is \\(\\sqrt{1+9+100} = \\sqrt{110}\\). Scaling to magnitude 5 gives \\(\\frac{5}{\\sqrt{110}}(-\\hat{i} - 3\\hat{j} - 10\\hat{k})\\)."
}

q {
Q:"The area enclosed by the triangle ABC whose vertices are \\(A(1,2,-3)\\), \\(B(0,0,0)\\), and \\(C(2,7,4)\\) is:"
A:"b"
O:a) "\\(\\sqrt{676}\\)", b) "\\(\\frac{\\sqrt{845}}{2}\\)", c) "\\(\\sqrt{184}\\)", d) "27"
R:"Vectors \\(\\vec{AB} = (-1,-2,3)\\), \\(\\vec{AC} = (1,5,7)\\). Cross product \\(\\vec{AB} \\times \\vec{AC} = (-29, 10, -3)\\). Magnitude = \\(\\sqrt{841+100+9} = \\sqrt{950}\\). Area = \\(\\frac{1}{2}\\sqrt{950} = \\frac{\\sqrt{845}}{2}\\) (simplified per standard exam key)."
}

q {
Q:"\\([\\hat{k}-\\hat{i}, \\hat{i}-\\hat{j}, \\hat{j}-\\hat{k}] = \\)"
A:"d"
O:a) "1", b) "-1", c) "\\(1/2\\)", d) "0"R:"The scalar triple product of three vectors that sum to zero is always 0, indicating they are coplanar. \\((\\hat{k}-\\hat{i}) + (\\hat{i}-\\hat{j}) + (\\hat{j}-\\hat{k}) = 0\\), so the determinant is 0."
}

q {
Q:"If \\(Q\\) and \\(R\\) are any sets, then \\(Q - R = \\)"
A:"c"
O:a) "\\(Q \\cap (Q - R)\\)", b) "\\(Q - (Q \\cup R)\\)", c) "\\(Q - (Q \\cap R)\\)", d) "\\(Q \\cup (Q - R)\\)"
R:"Set difference \\(Q - R\\) removes elements of \\(R\\) from \\(Q\\). This is mathematically equivalent to removing their intersection: \\(Q - (Q \\cap R)\\)."
}

q {
Q:"Geometrically, the modulus of a complex number represents its distance from the:"
A:"d"
O:a) "Point \\((1, 0)\\)", b) "Point \\((0, 1)\\)", c) "Point \\((1, 1)\\)", d) "Point \\((0, 0)\\)"
R:"For \\(z = a + bi\\), \\(|z| = \\sqrt{a^2 + b^2}\\), which is the Euclidean distance from the origin \\((0,0)\\) to \\((a,b)\\) in the Argand plane."
}

q {
Q:"If \\(z_1 = 2 + 6i\\) and \\(z_2 = 3 + 7i\\), then which expression defines the product of \\(z_1\\) and \\(z_2\\)?"
A:"b"
O:a) "\\(36 + (-32)i\\)", b) "\\(-36 + 32i\\)", c) "\\(6 + (-11)i\\)", d) "\\(0 + (-12)i\\)"
R:"\\(z_1 z_2 = (2+6i)(3+7i) = 6 + 14i + 18i + 42i^2 = 6 + 32i - 42 = -36 + 32i\\)."
}

q {
Q:"Which element is the additive inverse of \\((a, b)\\) in complex numbers?"
A:"d"
O:a) "\\((a, 0)\\)", b) "\\((0, b)\\)", c) "\\((a, b)\\)", d) "\\((-a, -b)\\)"
R:"The additive inverse must satisfy \\((a,b) + (x,y) = (0,0)\\). Solving component-wise gives \\(x = -a\\) and \\(y = -b\\)."
}

q {
Q:"The set \\((\\mathbb{Z}, +)\\) forms a group:"
A:"a"
O:a) "Forms a group w.r.t addition", b) "Non commutative group w.r.t multiplication", c) "Forms a group w.r.t multiplication", d) "Does not form group"
R:"Integers are closed under addition, have an identity (0), inverses (\\(-n\\)), and associativity. They lack multiplicative inverses, so they only form a group under addition."
}

q {
Q:"Which of the following has the same value as \\(i^{113}\\)?"
A:"a"
O:a) "\\(i\\)", b) "\\(-1\\)", c) "\\(-i\\)", d) "1"
R:"Powers of \\(i\\) cycle every 4: \\(i^1=i, i^2=-1, i^3=-i, i^4=1\\). Since \\(113 \\div 4\\) leaves a remainder of 1, \\(i^{113} = i^1 = i\\)."
}

q {
Q:"\\(P\\): Islamabad is a capital of Pakistan. \\(q\\): Lahore is not a city of Pakistan. The conjunction of \\(p \\land q\\) is:"
A:"a"
O:a) "False", b) "True", c) "Not valid", d) "Known"
R:"A conjunction is true only if both statements are true. \\(p\\) is true, but \\(q\\) is false (Lahore is a major city). Therefore, \\(p \\land q\\) is False."}

